  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Unity.TextMeshPro::TMPro.TextMeshProUGUI
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Rules: UTH is played in phases. The five phases are as follows\n\n<color=#cc2200>Place
    Bets</color> -> <color=#f58027>Pre-Flop</color> -> <color=#f5e427>Flop</color>
    -> <color=#2837fc>Turn/River</color> -> <color=#861eeb>Showdown</color>\n\n<color=#cc2200>Place
    Bets:</color> Before any cards are dealt, use the input field to wager a certain
    amount for the ante and blind. Minimum bet is $5 and max bet is $500. Leaving
    an empty input or typing a number outside of the min/max bounds will wager $10.
    Click deal to deal the cards. \n\n<color=#f58027>Pre-Flop:</color> Before the
    flop is dealt, you can bet 3x or 4x your ante wager as a \"play\" bet, or you
    can check (bet nothing) to see the flop. \n\n<color=#f5e427>Flop:</color> \nAfter
    flop is dealt, you can bet 2x the ante wager as a play bet, or you can check
    through to see the turn and river. \n\n<color=#2837fc>Turn/River:</color> After
    the turn and river are dealt, you can make a final play bet of 1x the ante, or
    you must fold. \n\n<color=#861eeb>Showdown:</color> Dealer flips over their hand
    and the best hand wins. Hand rankings are as follows and odds are as follows\n\nRoyal
    Flush (500:1) > Straight Flush (50:1) > 4 of a Kind (10:1) > Full House (5:1)
    > Flush (3:2) > Straight (1:1) > Three of a Kind (Even) > Two Pair (Even) > Pair
    (Even) > High Card (Even)\n\nPayouts are based on if the dealer \"qualifies\"
    meaning they have a pair or better ranking hand. A players ante and play bets
    can only be won back if the dealer qualifies. If the dealer fails to qualify,
    players get their pay and ante bets returned (push). Blind payouts are based
    on hand rankings and the odds listed previously. Players make profit by winning
    with a straight or better, and worse hands get the blind bet returned. If the
    dealer is qualified and wins, all bets are lost. Good luck!\n\n\n\n\n\n\n"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
